dataDictionary.Title: PDS4 Data Dictionary
dataDictionary.Description: This document is a dump of the contents of the PDS4 Data Dictionary

class.title: ASCII_Equivalent
class.description: The ASCII_Equivalent class contains attributes that identify and locate the ASCII data product equivalent to a given SEIS SEED data product.

class.title: ASCII_Equivalent_Internal_Reference
class.description: The Internal_Reference class is used to cross-reference other products in PDS4-compliant registries of PDS and its recognized international partners.

class.title: Metadata_Location
class.description: The Metadata_Location class contains attributes that identify and locate the metadata associated with a given SEIS data product.

class.title: Metadata_Location_Internal_Reference
class.description: The Internal_Reference class is used to cross-reference other products in PDS4-compliant registries of PDS and its recognized international partners.

class.title: Observation_Information
class.description: The Observation_Information class provides information about a science observation.

class.title: SEED_Equivalent
class.description: The SEED_Equivalent class contains attributes that identify and locate the SEED data product equivalent to a given SEIS ASCII data product.

class.title: SEED_Equivalent_Internal_Reference
class.description: The Internal_Reference class is used to cross-reference other products in PDS4-compliant registries of PDS and its recognized international partners.

class.title: SEIS_Instrument_Parameters
class.description: Attributes specific to the InSight Seismometer data products

attribute.title: ascii_equivalent_file_name
attribute.description: SEIS data products are archived in their native SEED format and in a PDS-compatible ASCII format. The ascii_equivalent_file_name attribute gives the name of the file that is the ASCII equivalent of a SEED format file.

attribute.title: metadata_file_name
attribute.description: SEIS observations are stored with the seismic data from the instrument in one file (mini-SEED or GeoCSV format) and the metadata for the measurements in another file (dataless SEED or StationXML format). The metadata_file_name attribute gives the name of the file containing the metadata associated with a given data file.

attribute.title: aobt_clock_start_count
attribute.description: The aobt_clock_start_count specifies the number of 1/1024 seconds recorded on the APSS On Board Time clock at the beginning of an observation.

attribute.title: aobt_clock_stop_count
attribute.description: The aobt_clock_stop_count specifies the number of 1/1024 seconds recorded on the APSS On Board Time clock at the end of an observation.

attribute.title: lobt_clock_start_count
attribute.description: The lobt_clock_start_count specifies the number of 1/1024 seconds recorded on the Lander On Board Time clock at the beginning of an observation.

attribute.title: lobt_clock_stop_count
attribute.description: The lobt_clock_stop_count specifies the number of 1/1024 seconds recorded on the Lander On Board Time clock at the end of an observation.

attribute.title: local_true_solar_time_sol
attribute.description: The local_true_solar_time_sol element specifies the number of solar days elapsed since a reference day (e.g. the day on which a landing vehicle set down) for local true solar time (LTST). Days are measured in rotations of the planet in question from midnight to midnight. The reference day is '0', as Landing day is Sol 0. If before Landing day, then value will be less than or equal to '0' and can be negative.

attribute.title: mars_year
attribute.description: The mars_year element specifies the number of the Mars year relative to the reference date of April 11, 1955 (Mars solar longitude 0), which is defined as the start of Mars year 1.

attribute.title: mission_phase_name
attribute.description: The mission_phase_name identifies a time period within the mission.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The ATLO mission phase (Assembly, Test, and Launch Operations) is the time of spacecraft and instrument assembly and test. During this phase data products are generated using flight hardware. They are usually not part of the final PDS archive but may be used for testing and peer review.

The cruise mission phase is from the time of escape from Earth's orbit through the time of entry into Mars' orbit. Some data products may be generated during this time, including instrument checkout data.

The development mission phase refers to the period of data processing software development and testing, before instruments are integrated with the spacecraft. Data products generated during this phase are usually not part of the final PDS archive but may be used for testing and peer review.
The surface mission phase is the time from arrival at Mars through the end of surface operations, including the primary mission and any extended missions that may take place.

The test mission phase is not a time period but a placeholder for the mission_phase_name value, used for data products generating during all project tests such as ORTs, SVTs and thread tests. Data products generated in this way are usually not part of the final PDS archive but may be used for testing and peer review.

attribute.title: release_number
attribute.description: Release_number is the number of a scheduled release of InSight data from PDS. The first Insight data release is Release 1a. The release_number for a given product is always the first release in which it appears, and does not change if the product is revised later.

attribute.title: software_name
attribute.description: Software_name identifies the processing software used to generate a data product.

attribute.title: software_version_id
attribute.description: Software_version_id identifies the version of the processing software used to generate a data product.

attribute.title: sol_number
attribute.description: Sol_number is the number of the Mars day on which an observation was acquired. Landing day is Sol 0.

attribute.title: spacecraft_clock_count_partition
attribute.description: The spacecraft_clock_count_partition provides the clock partition active for the spacecraft_clock_start_count and spacecraft_clock_stop_count attributes. This attribute may be used when the spacecraft_clock values do not include a partition number.

attribute.title: spacecraft_clock_start_count
attribute.description: The spacecraft_clock_start_count is the value of the spacecraft clock at the beginning of an observation. It represents the number of ticks. If a fractional value is present, it represents the number of 1/65536 ticks.

attribute.title: spacecraft_clock_stop_count
attribute.description: The spacecraft_clock_stop_count is the value of the spacecraft clock at the end of an observation.

attribute.title: start_local_mean_solar_time
attribute.description: Start_local_mean_solar_time is the local mean solar time, as defined in the main PDS4 data dictionary, at the beginning of an observation.

attribute.title: start_local_true_solar_time
attribute.description: Start_local_true_solar_time is the local true solar time, as defined in the main PDS4 data dictionary, at the beginning of an observation.

attribute.title: start_sol_number
attribute.description: Start_sol_number is the number of the Mars day on which a multiple-day observation was begun. Landing day is Sol 0.

attribute.title: start_solar_longitude
attribute.description: Start_solar_longitude is the solar longitude, as defined in the main PDS4 data dictionary, at the beginning of an observation.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: stop_local_mean_solar_time
attribute.description: Stop_local_mean_solar_time is the local mean solar time, as defined in the main PDS4 data dictionary, at the end of an observation.

attribute.title: stop_local_true_solar_time
attribute.description: Stop_local_true_solar_time is the local true solar time, as defined in the main PDS4 data dictionary, at the end of an observation.

attribute.title: stop_sol_number
attribute.description: Stop_sol_number is the number of the Mars day on which a multiple-day observation was ended. Landing day is Sol 0.

attribute.title: stop_solar_longitude
attribute.description: Stop_solar_longitude is the solar longitude, as defined in the main PDS4 data dictionary, at the end of an observation.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: seed_file_name
attribute.description: SEIS data products are archived in their native SEED format and in a PDS-compatible ASCII format. The seed_file_name attribute gives the name of the file that is the SEED equivalent of an ASCII data file.

attribute.title: channel_name
attribute.description: A SEIS data product contains data from a single location and single instrument channel. The channel_name uniquely identifies the location and channel pair using the format NN.AAA, where NN is a two-digit location number and AAA is a three-character channel code (letters or digits). The complete list of channel names may be found in the Channel Naming document in the SEIS document collection.

attribute.title: sample_count
attribute.description: Sample_count is the number of samples in a SEIS mini-SEED or GeoCSV product.

attribute.title: sampling_rate
attribute.description: Sampling_rate represents the number of samples per second (local on-board seconds). Because the instrument (EBox) clock drift is dependent on temperature, sampling_rate various over UTC time. However, this variation is small enough so as to be negligible and can be ignored for scientific analyses.
attribute.unitId: GHz, Hz, MHz, THz, kHz, mHz

attribute.title: seis_data_type
attribute.description: SEIS mini-SEED products and their equivalent GeoCSV products contain only seismic data, and therefore have the seis_data_type "waveform". SEIS dataless SEED products and their equivalent StationXML products contain only metadata for the seismic data files, and therefore have the seis_data_type "metadata".

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The data product contains only metadata.
The data product contains only seismic data.

attribute.title: seis_waveform_type
attribute.description: SEIS mini-SEED products and their equivalent GeoCSV products contain either continuous data, with one data product per UTC day, or event data, with one data product per event. An event may last several minutes. Continuous data products have seis_waveform_type "continuous". Event data products have seis_waveform_type "event".

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The data product contains continuous seismic data.
The data product contains event seismic data.

attribute.title: signal_name
attribute.description: The signal name is a short descriptive English name corresponding to a combination of SEIS channel code and location code. There are more than 1000 such combinations.
